title: Pregnant Rachael Finch shows off bikini body in Sydney | Daily Mail Online
text: Share 110 shares Looking radiant in the final weeks of pregnancy, the model sported a black lacy bikini top for the outing and mismatched pale pink bottoms. Not long now! The expectant star is set to give birth in a matter of weeks Not far off: The star's outing comes just weeks before she's due to give birth to her second child The former Miss Universe Australia's bronzed complexion glistened in the sun as she dipped in and out of the water. The sun-safe beauty added a black visor to her summery ensemble, while keeping her long locks tied up in a neat bun. The dance fitness coach strolled along the sands of the beach, stopping to chat to a friend along the way. Family fun: The 28-year-old was joined by her daughter Violet (pictured) and her husband Michael Miziner as they enjoyed a morning swim in Sydney Feeling good: The mum-to-be was seen proudly rubbing her belly as she soaked up the sun Bronzed beauty: The brunette stunner looked radiant as she took a dip in the water Rachael was seen cradling her baby bump as she spoke to the friend. Her husband Michael meanwhile, showed off his muscular physique in a pair of blue shorts. Their daughter Violet appeared to be enjoying her swim, as she was accompanied into the water by Rachael. Power couple: The brunette's husband Michael showed off his muscular physique in a pair of blue shorts Fit and fabulous: Rachael looked amazing in her mismatched bikini Doting mum: Rachael's three-year-old daughter Violet appeared to be enjoying the daytime swim Chatty: The mother-of-one was spotted cradling her belly while chatting to a friend on the beach Mama's princess: Little Violet was beaming as she sat on her mother's lap in the water Sharing: Rachael recently opened up about her varying experiences with her past and current pregnancy Rachael recently opened up about varying experiences with her current pregnancy compared to her first. 'It's so different and I didn't expect it to be so different,' she told Thinkergirl: The Podcast . The former Dancing With The Stars contestant explained how she had only '10 days of morning sickness' with Violet and has had 'four months straight of morning sickness' with her second baby. 'It's so different and I didn't expect it to be so different,' the former beauty queen said Tough times: The brunette explained how she had only '10 days of morning sickness' with Violet and has had 'four months straight of morning sickness' with her second baby Morning sickness: She went on to explain her morning sickness felt like 'food poisoning' '24 hours a day' Surprise: The certified health coach has also revealed she has yet to find out the gender of her unborn baby Busy: The expectant star has recently launched her own fitness program, Body Of Dance 'Think about a disgustingly long haul flight from somewhere like LA, with food poisoning,' she exclaimed. 'That is it, for 24 hours a day.' And the certified health coach also revealed she has yet to find out the gender of her unborn baby. Meanwhile, the Townsville-born model has not only juggled pregnancy and motherhood, but has also recently launched her own fitness program Body Of Dance. The workout program was created with her dancer husband Michael Miziner, whom she met while competing together on Dancing With The Stars in 2010. The dance partners fell in love on the reality show and married in 2013. Helping out: The model's fitness program helps people to get in shape via online dance workshops
